<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="161" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-12-06"><hi rend="italic">December 6,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that for the present and pending future arrangement of
                            the payment of the indemnity it is preferred that the United States
                            should not be placed in an exceptional position.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>